fields.name: Organic Irish Smoked Salmon 200g
fields.description:
Slowly smoked over smouldering oak in brick kilns on the West Coast of Scotland

Succulent & tender, with a delicate smoky taste. Delicious with a poached Daylesford Legbar egg on thin slices of our pumpernickel, or serve simply with fresh dill, a squeeze of lemon & creme fraiche.
Why Organic? We believe organic is better for our health, our animals and the environment; and of course always tastes better.

The fish are salted by hand and traditionally smoked in Inverawe's brick kilns, over gently smouldering oak log fires for up to 72 hours; depending on the weather. This careful, slow process results in rich, melt-in-the-mouth smoked salmon.
Features
Organic
Further Description
It's recommended that we eat at least 2 portions of fish a week, one of which should be oily fish such as salmon, rich in Omega 3 fatty acids.

Storage
Keep Refrigerated; Suitable for Home Freezing

fields.name: Beef Fillet Steak Typically: 200g
fields.description:
Min weight: 150g
Max weight: 250g
Our Ocado Beef Fillet steak is carefully selected and matured slowly over 21 days to deliver a succulent, tender and richly flavoured steak.

We mature all of our prime steak cuts for a minimum of 21 days a succulent and tender eat.

If you find your steak has become brown where the meat is touching the packaging or in-between steaks this is because meat needs air to stay red in colour and it is the lack of air between the steak and the packaging that has caused this discolouration. This is called contact discolouration and will not affect the safety or flavour of the product.

Storage
Keep refrigerated between -2C to +4C.

Once opened, use immediately.



Do not exceed the Use By date.



Suitable for freezing. Freeze on or before the Use By date. Use within 1 month. Defrost thoroughly before cooking and consume on day of defrosting. Do not refreeze.

Instructions
Cooking Instructions:
Remove all packaging. Wash hands, all surfaces and utensils after touching raw meat. Keep raw meat separate from cooked foods.

Not suitable for microwave cooking.

Pan Fry
Allow the steak to sit at room temperature for 10 minutes before cooking.

Preheat pan on high. Lightly oil and season steak. Place into a dry pan. Turn halfway through cooking Rare: 5-8 minutes, Medium: 7-10 minutes.

Allow to rest for 5 minutes before serving.

All appliances vary, these are guidelines only. Ensure product is piping hot before serving. Do not re-heat.

fields.name: Pork Fillet Medallions 300g
fields.description:
Our new range of pork cuts are from pigs that are free to roam outside and are fed on only vegetarian feed. The system guarantees that the piglets are born outdoors and reared without the use of antibiotics from birth. Such a high level of welfare means that there is a consistent supply of healthy, natural pig meat from happy pigs.
Features
Outdoor bred, Raised without antibiotics, Flavours without frontiers, RSPCA Assured

Storage
Cannot be cooked from Frozen; Cannot be Microwaved; Suitable for Home Freezing; Keep Refrigerated
Instructions
Shallow Fry - From Chilled. Always wash hands, all surfaces and utensils after handling raw meat.
Remove all packaging.
Preheat a little oil in a pan over a medium-high heat, carefully place the medallions in the pan and cook for the time specified above, turning occasionally. Drain before serving.
Ensure that the product is thoroughly cooked, no pink meat remains and the juices run clear.
Do not reheat.
No suitable for microwave cooking.
Not suitable for cooking from frozen.
All cooking appliances vary.
This is a guide only.

fields.name: Organic Pork Joint 1kg
fields.description:
Features
Organic
Storage
Keep Refrigerated; Suitable for Home Freezing
Instructions
Oven cook - From Chilled. For perfectly cooked pork, our head chef recommends:
Leg & Loin Joint: Season with salt, pepper and olive oil. Pan-fry until golden brown all over, then place in a hot oven (180C/fan 160C/Gas mk 4). Roast for 30 minutes per 500g, plus a further 30 minutes, until the pork is cooked through with no pink meat, and the juices run clear. Allow to rest for 5-10 minutes before serving.
Preparation and Usage
Wash hands, knives and surfaces thoroughly before and after preparing raw meat.
